1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:14,000
Here is the pain: two Codex sessions repeat the same failed deployment and correction.
Rules and unused skills accumulate, but nothing proves what should remain.

2
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:27,000
Agent memory asks what to add. Slime mold tests paths through use:
reinforce what works, withdraw what does not. Codex Metabolism applies that logic to collaboration.

3
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:40,000
This demo uses synthetic sessions. A friction candidate requires failure, a user correction,
the same command later succeeding, and the pattern repeating across two sessions.

4
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:54,000
One zero-install command stages CREATE HARNESS, PATCH RULE, KEEP SKILL, and RETIRE CANDIDATE.
Review writes only proposals; it never changes the live environment.

5
00:00:54,000 --> 00:01:09,000
Before creating anything, it climbs five rungs: necessity, Codex built-ins, installed capabilities,
repository assets, and reviewed open-source tools. If a rung is unchecked, creation is blocked.

6
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:23,000
The approved guard permits only the exact reviewed preflight-and-deploy sequence.
Echoes, OR operators, quoted text, subshells, and reordered commands are denied. Every change remains reversible.

7
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:38,000
After two later successful sessions, the next review returns KEEP HARNESS, VALIDATED.
An active receipt suppresses duplicate fixes, so the tool does not become another source of clutter.

8
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:53,000
The same loop keeps useful skills and marks an unused one as a retirement candidate only with complete lifecycle evidence.
A person approves archive or restore; nothing is silently deleted.

9
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:06,000
Across twenty-four synthetic cases: zero false positives, fifty percent recall.
The honest boundary is high precision, deliberate abstention, and no semantic clustering yet.

10
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:27,000
We built the core with Codex and GPT-5.6, using failing tests and cross-platform CI. In an optional live advisor run,
model gpt-5.6-sol agreed on CREATE HARNESS, challenged PATCH RULE with KEEP RULE, and could not override deterministic gates.

11
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Codex Metabolism: not just better skills.
Validate what works. Forget the rest.
